<subSubSection id="A6D16572E802FF8DFF1DE046FC4BF88E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EE7436F9E802FF8DFF1DE046FAFEFA16" blockId="6.[151,1437,752,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
However, 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFEE7E046FD79FAEA" authority="(Hancock, 1907)" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Pereira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[317,738,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFEE7E046FD80FAEA" box="[317,539,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Batrachidea planus</emphasis>
(Hancock, 1907)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFD31E046FCF6FAEA" bold="true" box="[747,877,1292,1318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C78C5790E802FF8DFD31E046FCF6FAEA" box="[747,877,1292,1318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is transferred here to this genus from 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFAFCE046FA0EFAEA" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1318,1429,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFAFCE046FA0EFAEA" box="[1318,1429,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tettigidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where it was originally described, adjusting better to the morphological characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFB43E07AFAB8FA86" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[1177,1315,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFB43E07AFAB8FA86" box="[1177,1315,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Batrachidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5A4B08E802FF8DFF4DE01EFE61FAA2" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Mendes, D. M. M. &amp; Silva, D. S. M. &amp; Cardona Granda, J. M. &amp; Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J." box="[151,506,1364,1390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1" refId="ref22188" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Mendes, D. M. M., Silva, D. S. M., Cardona Granda, J. M., Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J. (2019) Systematics and biogeography of the genus Scaria Bolivar, 1887 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Batrachideinae). Zootaxa, 4675 (1), 001 - 065. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4675.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cadena-Castañeda 
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFEB5E01FFE3AFAA2" box="[367,417,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFD45E01EFBBEFAA2" authority="Hebard, 1923" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1923" box="[671,1061,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFD45E01EFC1EFAA2" box="[671,901,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Batrachidea inermis</emphasis>
Hebard, 1923
</taxonomicName>
(female 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFB50E01EFB21FAA2" box="[1162,1210,1364,1390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
specimen) under 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFA5EE01FFF41FA5E" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFA5EE01FFF41FA5E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFEF0E032FEC1FA5E" box="[298,346,1400,1426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
specimen), both species” being conspecific. Now, when comparing the female 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFB01E032FA90FA5E" box="[1243,1291,1400,1426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFAE8E033FA06FA5E" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Pereira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1330,1437,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planus">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFAE8E033FA06FA5E" box="[1330,1437,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. planus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the female 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFE9FE0D6FEEEFA7A" box="[325,373,1436,1462]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFE46E0D7FD8BFA7A" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1923" box="[412,528,1437,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFE46E0D7FD8BFA7A" box="[412,528,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, no differences were found to keep both species separate (
<figureCitation id="76F02A7CE802FF8DFB7FE0D6FB6FFA7A" box="[1189,1268,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[169,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Batrachidea planus Hancock, 1907 comb. nov. (holotype of Batrachidea inermis Hebard, 1923) (A) right lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614409" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614409/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="76F02A7CE802FF8DFADBE0D6FA8AFA7A" box="[1281,1297,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@14.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Batrachidea planus Hancock, 1907 comb. nov. (holotype of Tettigidea planus Hancock, 1907) (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: University Museum, Hope Entomological Collections (UMO), Oxford, photo modificated from Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614411/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">9</figureCitation>
). Thus, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C78C5790E802FF8DFAB4E0D6FE97FA16" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">new synonymy</taxonomicNameLabel>
is proposed: 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFE78E08AFCDAFA16" authority="(Hancock, 1907)" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Pereira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[418,833,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planus">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFE78E08AFDE5FA16" box="[418,638,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Batrachidea planus</emphasis>
(Hancock, 1907)
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFC85E08AFB6CFA16" authority="(Hancock, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[863,1271,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFC85E08AFBA8FA16" box="[863,1075,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Batrachidea brevis</emphasis>
(Hancock, 1909)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFB24E08AFAFEFA16" bold="true" box="[1278,1381,1472,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C78C5790E802FF8DFB24E08AFAFEFA16" box="[1278,1381,1472,1498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE7436F9E802FF8DFF1DE0AEFC4BF88E" blockId="6.[151,1437,752,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFF1DE0AEFDC9FA32" authority="Bruner, 1913" authorityName="Bruner" authorityYear="1913" box="[199,594,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFF1DE0AEFE29FA32" box="[199,434,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tettigidea granulosa</emphasis>
Bruner, 1913
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFD86E0AEFD5CFA32" bold="true" box="[604,711,1508,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C78C5790E802FF8DFD86E0AEFD5CFA32" box="[604,711,1508,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="76F02A7CE802FF8DFD00E0AEFCBBFA33" box="[730,800,1508,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[184,1402,181,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[184,1402,181,1879]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Batrachidea mucronata (Saint-Fargeau &amp; Serville, 1825) (holotype of Tettigidea granulosa Bruner, 1913 syn. nov.) (A) left lateral view, (B) right lateral view, (C) dorsal view with arrows highlighting the anterior margin of pronotum (above the occiput, in dorsal view) undulated, (D) frontal view and (E) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614405/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) is proposed as a synonym under 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFB6EE0AFFAD5FA32" baseAuthorityName="Saint-Fargeau &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[1204,1358,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFB6EE0AFFAD5FA32" box="[1204,1358,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, when comparing with the characteristics of both species, these are coincident. 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFC19E343FBCAF9EE" authorityName="Bruner" authorityYear="1913" box="[963,1105,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFC19E343FBCAF9EE" box="[963,1105,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
conforms to a macropronotal form of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFF2CE367FE14F98A" baseAuthorityName="Saint-Fargeau &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[246,399,1581,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFF2CE367FE14F98A" box="[246,399,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, complying with the range of variation described by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5A4B08E802FF8DFC2BE366FB1CF98B" author="Grant Jr., H. J." box="[1009,1159,1580,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="67 - 108" refId="ref22611" refString="Grant Jr., H. J. (1956) The taxonomy of Batrachidea, Puiggaria, Lophoscirtus, Eutettigidea and Rehnidium n. gen. (Orthotpera: Acridoidea, Tetrigidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 82, 67 - 108." type="journal article" year="1956">Grant (1956)</bibRefCitation>
. Similar structure of the frontal costa, as in frontal and profile view, brown coloration as the 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFC53E31AFC22F9A6" box="[905,953,1616,1642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFB82E31BFA07F9A6" authority="Bruner, 1910" authorityName="Bruner" authorityYear="1910" box="[1112,1436,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilicornis">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFB82E31BFA9FF9A6" box="[1112,1284,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. gracilicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8A5A4B08E802FF8DFAD0E31AFA07F9A6" author="Bruner, L." box="[1290,1436,1616,1642]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="89 - 143" refId="ref22024" refString="Bruner, L. (1910) South American Tetrigidae. Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 7, 89 - 143." type="journal article" year="1910">Bruner, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(currently synonymous of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFE65E33FFDCDF942" baseAuthorityName="Saint-Fargeau &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[447,598,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFE65E33FFDCDF942" box="[447,598,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the small spot near the apex of the usual tegmina of this species. The only character found in the 
<typeStatus id="3170885BE802FF8DFE17E3D2FE66F97E" box="[461,509,1688,1714]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFD4EE3D3FCBAF97E" authorityName="Bruner" authorityYear="1913" box="[660,801,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFD4EE3D3FCBAF97E" box="[660,801,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the shape of the anterior edge of the pronotum, which is “wavy”, without the spine of the anterior edge of the pronotum, but when reading the original description of this species it does not describe this characteristic so unusual in 
<taxonomicName id="29CB4D7AE802FF8DFC98E3AAFC76F936" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[834,1005,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Batrachideinae">Batrachideinae</taxonomicName>
, that Bruner most certainly would not have overlooked for the description of this species, suggesting that the current shape of the anterior border of the pronotum is damage to this region, subsequent to the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A6D16572E802FF8DFF1DE206FAD2F8AB" box="[199,1353,1868,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EE7436F9E802FF8DFF1DE206FAD2F8AB" blockId="6.[151,1437,752,1895]" box="[199,1353,1868,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="DCBFEAEBE802FF8DFF1DE206FEFAF8AA" bold="true" box="[199,353,1868,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
South America, from Colombian to South 
<collectingCountry id="96DC7669E802FF8DFC99E206FC03F8AA" box="[835,920,1868,1894]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, central 
<collectingCountry id="96DC7669E802FF8DFC2CE206FBC5F8AA" box="[1014,1118,1868,1894]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="96DC7669E802FF8DFB4FE206FB42F8AA" box="[1173,1241,1868,1894]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="76F02A7CE802FF8DFB33E206FAA7F8AB" box="[1257,1340,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1767,1791]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1101,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-428@43.[151,1436,1101,1743]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 35. Map of approximated occurrence of the genus Batrachidea Serville, 1838." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614464/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
